parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine head gasket failure can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and even engine compartment fires, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: white smoke emitted through exhaust pipes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition coil failure can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and difficulty starting the engine, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Timing chain guide failure can cause engine damage, loss of power, and abnormal engine sounds, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the driver's side seat belt can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality in the event of a collision, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to retract
the seat belt does not lock during impact
the seat belt cannot be unlatched
the seat belt does not restrain the occupant when brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
difficulty steering when the engine is cold.
